# Styling

- Use HeroUI (previously NextUI) components whenever possible.
- Use Tailwind for styling.

# Project structure

- Put repositories in `data/repositories`. Use naming like `sets.repository.ts` (dot notation).
- Put services in `services`. Use naming like `sets.service.ts` (dot notation).
- Don't use barrel files (index.ts re-exports). Import from direct file paths.
- Always use absolute imports (`@/...`).

# Types

- Colocate types with where they originate. Don't use separate `types.ts` files.
- Rely on TypeScript inference when possible. Don't export helper-like types unnecessarily.
- For view models with conversion logic, use a namespace merge: export the type and a namespace with the same name containing a static factory (e.g. `SetsListViewModel.fromSetViewModels(sets)`). Keep conversion out of services.

# Repository pattern

- Repositories accept their data source explicitly in the constructor (e.g. `new SetsRepository(bionicleSets)`).
- Data retrieval lives in the repository; data manipulation and domain logic live in the service.
- Focus on testability: inject data sources so tests can use dummy data without complex mocking.

# Dependency injection

- Use class-based services and repositories with constructor injection.
- Services receive their dependencies (e.g. repository) in the constructor; the service calls the repository internally.
- Define a port/interface in the service for the repository shape it needs; the concrete repository satisfies it structurally.
- Export a default instance for production: `setsService = new SetsService(setsRepository)`.
- Tests inject a mock: `new SetsService(new SetsRepository(mockData))` — no mocking framework needed.

# Server actions

- Use next-safe-action's `useAction` hook with callbacks (`onError`, `onSuccess`) instead of manual `useTransition` + result handling.
- For action error toasts, use `getActionErrorMessage` from utils (uses `flattenValidationErrors` from next-safe-action)

# Services

- Services should return the view model shape the UI needs. Avoid calling multiple services in a page when one can return the full view model (e.g. `getCollectionListViewModel` instead of flat list + separate grouping).

# Components

- Colocate components that are only used together in the same file. Only export the top-level component that is used externally.
- Data fetching can happen inside the component that needs the data; the page renders the component and doesn't need to wire data.
- Extract shared typography (PageTitle, SectionHeading, SubsectionHeading) to reusable components in `components/typography`.

# Testing

- Mock repositories accept `Partial<RepositoryPort>` as overrides. Use plain `vi.fn()` by default; no default resolved values. Tests pass mock implementations explicitly (e.g. `getUserCollection: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(["1"])`).

# Code organization

- Order functions from general to specific: broader context first, then details. Main/exported function at the top, helpers below in the order they are used.
